Essentially, they are highly processed carbohydrates derived from wheat – meaning that the protein (gluten) portion should have been fully separated from it. The operative phrase is: "should have been." It usually is, and as a result, it's not uncommon to see products that contain these ingredients bearing a "gluten-free" claim.
